snippet.textDisplay:
Yet another horrifying time-for-open-play scripted match in another weekend of awful fixed football - all over Europe and the world, leagues are at minimum encouraging teams to score either early or very late in each half, with stoppage-time goals being optimal. Otherwise, fluke goals - deflections, crazy angles, and obvious penalties - are the permitted exceptions, with the addition of compensation goals, where a team scores outside the prescribed time and the other team is allowed either to score or to try to score (depending, presumably, on how much money is riding on side bets and whether the outcome itself is fixed). The big leagues go further, following American sports and the English Premier League, and massage the weekly matches to shape the storylines of the season.

This destroys the on-field product and many careers, especially for strikers who go off form while their teams are scheduled to lose or who just lose the touch while purposely missing or seeking deflections for most of the minutes of every game (when they get chances at all).

It was not always so, but this format has taken over worldwide in the last few years. First was England, roughly from when Ronaldo left MU, and the UEFA competitions joined in thereafter. Since then, it has subsumed pretty much all of FIFA. In all cases, it is a top-down thing, “for the good of football”, and the only players who would like it are lazy players. The players are just the performers, the employees.

It kills me to say this, but the money people are killing the world’s most popular sport, just to vampirize even more money, from more siphons, from the mostly poor and working class fan base. I have never needed the simple diversion of football more than I have in recent years, and the sport just gets worse and worse while the training and athleticism and greater knowledge base should be bringing it to new heights. The corruption is in all of our faces weekly, and I have to keep pointing it out. If we say nothing it will not stop.
